  "text": "Because VEGF is a marker for angiogenesis, blocking the angiogenic process may represent a promising way of treating the tumor. Studies have shown that androgen regulates VEGF content in prostate cancer [CITATION_1] . As cannabis extract treatment resulted in a decrease in androgen receptor expression, the effects on VEGF were also determined. It was observed that cannabis extract treatment resulted in a dose dependent decrease in VEGF mRNA expression ( Figure 5(b) ).",
